<div id="review_2906292586" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2906292586" />
    <a title="Swaroop" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop"><img alt="Swaroop" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621672092p2/100264072.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2906292586?book_show_action=true">Jul 22, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Swaroop" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Swaroop" href="/user/show/100264072-swaroop">Swaroop</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9781427213723" href="/book/show/33016123-the-righteous-mind">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2906292586" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1702472648908750470">&quot;<i>We are 90% chimp and 10% being.</i>&quot;<br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11324722.The_Righteous_Mind_Why_Good_People_Are_Divided_by_Politics_and_Religion' title='The Righteous Mind Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion by Jonathan Haidt' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Righteous Mind: Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion</a> is much more than just about &quot;Why good people are divided by politics and religion&quot;. It is a <b>detailed, descriptive and a very interesting</b> facts-based investigation and research into the origins of morality and righteousness. Morality is explained and defined in different ways in this book.<br/><br/><i>&quot;There is more in man than the breath of his body.&quot;</i><br/><br/><i>&quot;We, humans, have extraordinary capability to care ab</i></span>
  <span id="freeText1702472648908750470" style="display:none">"<i>We are 90% chimp and 10% being.</i>"<br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11324722.The_Righteous_Mind_Why_Good_People_Are_Divided_by_Politics_and_Religion" title="The Righteous Mind Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion by Jonathan Haidt" rel="nofollow noopener">The Righteous Mind: Why Good People Are Divided by Politics and Religion</a> is much more than just about "Why good people are divided by politics and religion". It is a <b>detailed, descriptive and a very interesting</b> facts-based investigation and research into the origins of morality and righteousness. Morality is explained and defined in different ways in this book.<br /><br /><i>"There is more in man than the breath of his body."</i><br /><br /><i>"We, humans, have extraordinary capability to care about things beyond our capacity."</i><br /><br /><i>"The human mind is a story processor, not a logic processor."</i><br /><br />This book provides a deeper understanding of the human being's thinking. It's focus is to understand each other's personality and our way of thinking, and to coexist peacefully. [NOT fight, segregate and discriminate (and build walls).]<br /><br /><i>"I am a small rider on a very big elephant."</i><br /><br /><b>
  <i>"We are all stuck here for a while, so let's try to work it out."</i>
</b> Love is the answer, above everything else.<br /><br />Thought provoking, and a fun read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="1702472648908750470" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


